dyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104mwa1665702688914.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/mwa1665702688914.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/mwa1665702688914.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"mwa1665702688914\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Modeled Component\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">This property specifies the name of the modeled component from which this component is derived.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"mwa1665702688914__section_w1106ab1b5b1_w1107ab1b5_w1108ab1\">\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"mwa1665702688914__table_d10919e1_d10920e1_d10921e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Technical Name: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> MODELED_TEMPLATE </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Expected Value: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> String of up to 32 characters. Supports\n                        Unicode. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Default Value: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> None </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"mwa1665702688914__section_mb1_xbk_4wb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d739131e94\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"mwa1665702688914__p_d97367e1_d97368e1_d97369e1\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"uhr1704434505611.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/uhr1704434505611.html\" title=\"A modeled component is an abstract component definition that specifies a data structure, layout, and code for components that share a common purpose or similar behavior. It is used to create new components, known as derived components, which can inherit component-level changes made in the modeled component.\">Modeled Components</a>.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"mwa1665702688914__section_rx1_bck_4wb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d739131e113\">Applies To</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"mwa1665702688914__ul_xc1_cck_4wb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"mwa1665702688914__li_d39968e1_d39969e1_d39970e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ifc1665702608950.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ifc1665702608950.html\" title=\"A Component is a Main Development Object that defines an executable part of an application. It defines the data structure used to access data, the layout (if applicable) used to present it, and the actions used to modify, validate, and store data.\">Component</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3614697\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3614697\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Modeled Component Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 09, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Modeled Component This property specifies the name of the modeled component from which this component is derived. Technical Name: MODELED_TEMPLATE Expected Value: String of up to 32 characters. Supports Unicode. Default Value: None Description For more information, see Modeled Components . Applies To Component Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}